{"type":"message","id":"26ef195d","parentId":"1c82f280","timestamp":"2026-03-24T15:45:39.383Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_d3kgrputk90e_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 114415\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what single concrete action would advance the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent state:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 COMPLETE\r\n- CFI Analysis done - found that 44.8% of invariants are pure noise (CFI=0)\r\n- Next pending action: CFI-weighted compression experiment\r\n\r\nThe most impactful next action would be to implement the CFI-weighted compression experiment. This involves:\r\n1. Using CFI scores to weight compression decisions\r\n2. Comparing next-pulse prediction quality vs frequency baseline\r\n\r\nLet me think about what concrete file edit would advance this. I could:\r\n1. Create a script that implements CFI-weighted compression\r\n2. Create a test comparing CFI-weighted vs frequency-weighted compression\r\n3. Update the CFI_RESULTS.md with next steps\r\n\r\nGiven the \"one concrete action\" constraint, I should pick the most impactful single thing. The natural next step from CFI analysis is to implement a CFI-weighted compression mechanism.\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files exist and what would be a good next step. I need to create something that advances the CFI-weighted compression experiment.\r\n\r\nI'll create a new script that:\r\n1. Loads the CFI scores from the analysis\r\n2. Implements CFI-weighted compression\r\n3. Can be run to compare with frequency baseline\r\n\r\nActually, let me be more concrete. The experiment needs:\r\n- A way to test if CFI-weighted compression improves next-pulse prediction\r\n- A comparison with frequency-based baseline\r\n\r\nThe most direct action would be to create a compression experiment script that implements both approaches and can measure prediction quality.\r\n\r\nLet me write a pulse script modification or a new experiment script.\r\n\r\nActually, I think the best single action is to create a `scripts/cfi_compression_experiment.ps1` that:\r\n1. Implements CFI-weighted compression selection\r\n2. Implements frequency-baseline compression selection  \r\n3. Tests both on the existing invariant data\r\n\r\n\r\n4. Provides metrics for comparison\r\n\r\nI'll develop a script to benchmark the compression strategies, focusing on quantifiable performance differences between CFI-weighted and frequency-based approaches. The goal is to create a reproducible experiment that can objectively measure prediction quality improvements.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nCFI analysis revealed that 44.8% of invariants are pure noise (CFI=0), while only 5.7% are true causal anchors (CFI>=0.7). The next logical step is implementing and testing CFI-weighted compression against the frequency baseline to see if it improves next-pulse prediction.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a CFI-weighted compression experiment script that compares CFI-weighted selection vs frequency-baseline selection, enabling quantitative validation of whether CFI scoring actually improves compression quality.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\n# Compares CFI-weighted compression vs frequency baseline\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [string]$InvariantFile = \"research/frequency_invariants.md\",\r\n    [string]$OutputFile = \"research/cfi_compression_results.md\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n# Load CFI scores from previous analysis\r\n$cfiData = @{\r\n    \"session_gap_detection\" = @{ freq = 45; cfi = 0.82; type = \"research_trajectory\" }\r\n    \"pulse_timing\" = @{ freq = 58; cfi = 0.91; type = \"research_trajectory\" }\r\n    \"goal_tracking\" = @{ freq = 52; cfi = 0.78; type = \"research_trajectory\" }\r\n    \"error_format\" = @{ freq = 60; cfi = 0.01; type = \"constant_format\" }\r\n    \"timestamp_pattern\" = @{ freq = 60; cfi = 0.0; type = \"noise\" }\r\n    \"file_path_format\" = @{ freq = 60; cfi = 0.0; type = \"noise\" }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Strategy 1: Frequency baseline (current approach)\r\n$freqBaseline = $cfiData.GetEnumerator() | Sort-Object -Property { $_.Value.freq } -Descending | Select-Object -First 10\r\n\r\n# Strategy 2: CFI-weighted (proposed approach)\r\n# Weight = cfi * log(freq + 1) to balance persistence and frequency\r\n$cfiWeighted = $cfiData.GetEnumerator() | ForEach-Object {\r\n    $weight = $_.Value.cfi * [Math]::Log($_.Value.freq + 1)\r\n    [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n        Name = $_.Key\r\n        CFI = $_.Value.cfi\r\n        Freq = $_.Value.freq\r\n        Weight = $weight\r\n        Type = $_.Value.type\r\n    }\r\n} | Sort-Object -Property Weight -Descending | Select-Object -First 10\r\n\r\n# Filter analysis\r\n$noiseFiltered = $cfiData.GetEnumerator() | Where-Object { $_.Value.cfi -gt 0.7 }\r\n$constantFiltered = $cfiData.GetEnumerator() | Where-Object { $_.Value.cfi -eq 0 -and $_.Value.freq -eq 60 }\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"=== CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment ===\"\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Frequency Baseline (top 10 by freq):\"\r\n$freqBaseline | ForEach-Object { Write-Host \"  $($_.Key): freq=$($_.Value.freq), cfi=$($_.Value.cfi)\" }\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\nWrite-Host \"CFI-Weighted (top 10 by weight = cfi * log(freq+1)):\"\r\n$cfiWeighted | ForEach-Object { Write-Host \"  $($_.Name): cfi=$($_.CFI), freq=$($_.Freq), weight=$([Math]::Round($_.Weight,3))\" }\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Key Differences:\"\r\nWrite-Host \"  -\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 11:44:43\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774367139381}}
