{"type":"message","id":"bcbf8ab1","parentId":"bab25509","timestamp":"2026-03-24T15:45:50.553Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_67y40r9nwfjh_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 114517\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: a (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine a concrete action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals and recent work:\r\n1. CFI Analysis is complete - found that 44.8% of invariants have CFI=0 (pure noise), only 5.7% have high CFI (>=0.7)\r\n2. The next pending action is the CFI-weighted compression experiment\r\n\r\nThe CFI_RESULTS.md document exists and contains the analysis. The key insight is that we need to:\r\n- Distinguish between process artifacts (CFI=0) and research trajectory (CFI>0.7)\r\n- Implement CFI filtering\r\n- Run a compression experiment comparing CFI-weighted vs frequency baseline\r\n\r\nA concrete next action would be to:\r\n1. Create a simple script or analysis that extracts the high-CFI invariants (>=0.7) from the existing analysis\r\n2. Compare next-pulse prediction quality between CFI-weighted selection vs frequency-only selection\r\n\r\nLet me look at what data we have. The CFI_RESULTS.md document analyzed invariants from... looking at the results, it seems they found 44.8% have CFI=0, 5.7% have high CFI >=0.7.\r\n\r\nA concrete action: Create a CFI-weighted compression experiment plan or script that:\r\n1. Loads the existing invariant data\r\n2. Implements CFI-weighted selection\r\n3. Compares against frequency baseline\r\n\r\nOr I could add to the CFI_RESULTS.md document a concrete next-steps section that defines the experiment more precisely.\r\n\r\nActually, let me be more specific. The pending task is \"CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline)\". \r\n\r\nA concrete action would be to:\r\n1. Update CFI_RESULTS.md with a defined experiment protocol, OR\r\n2. Create a small script/analysis that begins implementing this\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete next-steps section in CFI_RESULTS.md that defines the experiment clearly, with specific metrics and methodology. This would be a file edit that advances the pending goal.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI_RESULTS.md document established that 5.7% of invariants have high CFI (>=0.7) representing true causal anchors, while 44.8% are pure noise (CFI=0). The natural next step is to design the CFI-weighted compression experiment to validate this finding empirically.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nAdd a concrete experiment protocol to CFI_RESULTS.md that defines the methodology for comparing CFI-weighted selection against frequency baseline, enabling the next pulse to implement and run the experiment.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```markdown\r\n## Experiment Protocol: CFI-Weighted Compression\r\n\r\n### Objective\r\nValidate that CFI-weighted selection produces better next-pulse prediction than frequency-only baseline.\r\n\r\n### Method\r\n1. **Corpus**: Use existing pulse artifacts (pulse_*.md files)\r\n2. **Frequency Baseline**: Select top-K invariants by frequency (current approach)\r\n3. **CFI-Weighted**: Select top-K invariants by CFI score (proposed approach)\r\n4. **Metric**: Compare prediction accuracy on held-out pulse content\r\n\r\n### Specific Experiment Design\r\n```\r\nK values to test: 10, 25, 50, 100\r\n\r\nFor each K:\r\n  - Baseline: Select top-K by frequency\r\n  - CFI-Weighted: Select top-K by CFI (filtering CFI=0 invariants first)\r\n  - Test on next unseen pulse\r\n  - Measure: token overlap, semantic similarity (embedding cosine)\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected Outcome\r\n- CFI-weighted should preserve \"research trajectory\" invariants (CFI>0.7)\r\n- CFI-weighted should exclude \"process artifacts\" (CFI=0)\r\n- Prediction quality should improve for CFI-weighted at same K\r\n\r\n### Implementation Notes\r\n- Use `research/invariants/invariant_analysis.md` data for CFI scores\r\n- Compare selection sets: identify which invariants are in one but not other\r\n- Measure Jaccard similarity between selection sets at each K\r\n```markdown\r\nfile: research/CFI_RESULTS.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 11:45:39\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774367150552}}
